        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 3:25PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms with gusty
winds along a line extending from Chula to near Spainville to near
Blackstone.
Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and brief heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Blackstone, Scotts Fork, Fort Barfoot, Spainville, and Chula
around 330 PM EDT.
Mannboro and Wilsons around 335 PM EDT.
Moseley around 340 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include North Wellville,
Irby, Earls, Pilkinton, Ammon, Murdocks, Forkland, Darvills,
Winterham, and Pocahontas State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
